/target
/dist
**/*.rs.bk

# The raw Lichess dump (~290 MB compressed, ~1.1 GB raw). Never committed; the
# curation tool downloads it on demand into this scratch directory. Only the
# curated subset in `database/` is tracked.
/.cache/

# Throwaway probes. CLAUDE.md tells you to write one to check a fixture's claim
# before building tests on it, so they will keep appearing; this stops them being
# swept up by `git add -A`. Anything worth keeping is a real test, not a probe.
**/examples/probe*.rs
**/tests/probe*.rs

# Review-agent scratch worktrees.
/target-review/

# Node / Playwright, for the browser test in `crates/blindfold-web`. The built
# bundle and the browser downloads are regenerated; only the spec is tracked.
node_modules/
dist/
/crates/blindfold-web/test-results/
/crates/blindfold-web/playwright-report/
/crates/blindfold-web/blob-report/
/crates/blindfold-web/.playwright/

# Editors / OS / tooling.
.vs/
.idea/
.vscode/
.DS_Store
*.pdb
/.playwright-mcp/

# Dev-loop debris. The sibling `dexterity` repo has accumulated 152 stray
# screenshots and 55 dev logs in its root by not having these — the app-driving
# and screenshot workflows genuinely do produce them, so they are pre-empted here
# rather than learned the hard way. Deliberate artefacts can be force-added.
dev.*.log
*.png
